               <msContents>
                  <summary>Author <persName role="cmm" key="person_90747748"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90747748/" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muṣṭafà Şem‘ī
                        (d. ca. 1602.)</persName> composed this Ottoman Turkish commentary on the
                     Persian <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Pandnāmah</title> (Book of Advice),
                     spuriously ascribed to <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard"
                        key="person_120724759" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/120724759/" role="dub"
                        >Farīd al-Dīn ʻAṭṭār</persName>. In his introduction, the author states how
                     he composed the work at the request of his friend, Ṣāḥib al-Dawlah ʿÖmer bin
                     Ḥüseyin, which he dedicated to the latter’s patron Zeyrek Ağa, then presented
                     it to <persName role="hnr" key="person_266879898"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/266879898/">Sulṭān Murād III (b. 1546, r. 1574–95
                        CE)</persName> when completed. The commentary itself consists of verse by
                     verse quotations, with their translations, and occasional glosses on the
                     original text, a style that the author maintains in his other Ottoman
                     commentaries on Persian works. An Ottoman-era scribe named <persName
                        xml:lang="tu">Ahmet Kadır Bülevi</persName> completed this manuscript <date
                        calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1666-07-06">3 Muḥarram 1077 AH (6 Jul. 1666
                        CE)</date>. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_889-item1">
                     <author role="dub" key="person_120724759" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/120724759/"
                        change="#ids-cleanup #role-assignment">
