                  <additions><lb/>
                     <label>Inscriptions:</label><list>
                        <item> the <locus from="ib" to="ib">first right flyleaf b side (f.
                              ib)</locus> bears a pious Arabic phrase in rıḳʿa and an Arabic
                           religious text in thirteen lines of Kufic script.</item>
                        <item><locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus> bears lines Turkish and Persian
                           poetry (with <hi rend="italic">abjad</hi> numbers), pious phrases in
                           Arabic, and a list of alms with amounts in dirhams to be spent in memory
                           of six shaykhs.</item>
                        <item>Folio <locus from="67b" to="67b">67b</locus> features an prayer in
                           Arabic alongside the colophon, and what may be a Sufi <hi rend="italic"
                              >vaẓīfah</hi> (Turkish: <hi rend="italic">vezife</hi>) at top,
                           indicating recitation of three <hi rend="italic">istighfār</hi>
                           (repentance) and the Divine name <hi rend="italic">al-Jalīl</hi> (the
                           Glorious) a thousand times.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1700" notAfter="1800">
                        <p>Rebound in the <placeName cert="high"
                              ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7024412" key="place_7024412"
                              >Ottoman empire</placeName> in the <date calendar="#Gregorian"
                              from="1700" to="1800">18th century CE</date>.</p>
                        <p>Sewn at two stations in yellow silk thread. Edges trimmed with twined
                           chevron endbands at <locus from="Head" to="Head">head</locus> and <locus
                              from="Tail" to="Tail">tail</locus>. Covered in full red goatskin
                              <material>leather</material>, without a flap (Type III binding per
                           Déroche). Internal pastedowns and flyleaves of 18th-century style Ottoman
                           marbled papers (Persian <hi rend="italic">abrī</hi>, Ottoman: <hi
                              rend="italic">ebrī</hi>, 'clouded') feature large indigo craquelure
                           (Turkish: <hi rend="italic">ḳumlū</hi>, 'sandy') spots over a spattered
                           ground of dark indigo and ochre.</p>
                        <p>Subsequently rebacked in goatskin <material>leather</material> and the
                           internal hinges replaced with the same, probably in the <date
                              calendar="#Gregorian" from="1900" to="1990">20th century CE</date></p>
                        <decoNote type="binding">Title written on the tail edge:<lb/>
                           <q xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc">Pend Şerḥ-i Şemʿī</q></decoNote>
                        <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                              <height>192</height>
                              <width>129</width>
                              <depth>18</depth>
                           </dimensions></p>
                        <condition>Handle binding with caution, in fair condition, with abrasion to
                           the exterior. Stiff opening due to restoration. Boxed.</condition>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
